    "body": "this has been failing frequently. ~~could it be related to the \"busted\" refactor @lewis6991 ? It looks like the metatable is compared sometimes, did luaassert ignore that previously?~~ er, `exitcode` is different, the metatable is probably not the important part.\n\n```\nFAILED   ...vim/build/Xtest_xdg_api/test/functional/api/vim_spec.lua @ 2933: API nvim_list_chans, nvim_get_chan_info stream=job :terminal channel\nExpected values to be equal.\nExpected:\n{\n  argv = { \"/home/runner/work/neovim/neovim/build/bin/shell-test\", \"INTERACT\" },\n  buf = 3,\n  buffer = 3,\n  exitcode = 129,\n  id = 5,\n  mode = \"terminal\",\n  pty = \"\",\n  stream = \"job\"\n}\nActual:\n{\n  argv = { \"/home/runner/work/neovim/neovim/build/bin/shell-test\", \"INTERACT\" },\n  buf = 3,\n  buffer = 3,\n  exitcode = 0,\n  id = 5,\n  mode = \"terminal\",\n  pty = \"\",\n  stream = \"job\",\n  <metatable> = {\n    __tostring = <function 1>\n  }\n}\nstack traceback:\n\t...vim/build/Xtest_xdg_api/test/functional/api/vim_spec.lua:2990: in function <...vim/build/Xtest_xdg_api/test/functional/api/vim_spec.lua:2933>\n```",
